<exercisegroup><introduction><p>In Problems 27–30, use the graph to estimate the solution to the equation or inequality. Show the solution or solutions on the graph. Then check your answers algebraically.</p></introduction>

    <exercise number="27"><statement><p>
        The figure shows a graph of <m>f (x) = \sqrt{x} - 2</m>, for <m>x\gt 0</m>. Solve the following:</p><p>
        <sidebyside width="60%"><image source="images/fig-2-2-27"><description>square root shifted</description></image></sidebyside> 
        <ol label="a" cols="2">
            <li><p><m>\sqrt{x} - 2=1.5</m></p></li>
            <li><p><m>\sqrt{x} - 2=2.25</m></p></li>
            <li><p><m>\sqrt{x} - 2\lt 1</m></p></li>
            <li><p><m>\sqrt{x} - 2\gt -0.25</m></p></li>
        </ol>
    </p></statement>
    <answer><p><ol label="a" cols="4">
        <li><p><m>x\approx 12</m></p></li>
        <li><p><m>x\approx 18</m></p></li>
        <li><p><m>x \lt 9</m></p></li>
        <li><p><m>x\gt 3</m></p></li>
    </ol></p></answer>
    </exercise>

