<exercisegroup cols="2"><introduction><p>
    In Problems 59<ndash/>64, decide whether each statement is true for all values of <m>a</m> and <m>b</m>. If the statement is true, give an algebraic justification. If it is false, find values of <m>a</m> and <m>b</m> to disprove it.
    <ol label="a" cols="2">
        <li><p><m>f (a + b) = f (a) + f (b)</m></p></li>
        <li><p><m>f (ab) = f (a)f (b)</m></p></li>
    </ol>
</p></introduction>

    <exercise number="59"><statement><p><m>f(x)=x^2 </m></p></statement>
    <answer><p><ol label="a">
        <li><p>Not always true: <m>f (1 + 2)\ne f (1) + f (2)</m> because <m>9\ne 5</m>.</p></li>
        <li><p>True: <m>(ab)^2 = a^2b^2</m></p></li>
    </ol></p></answer>
    </exercise>

