    <exercise number="63"><statement><p><m>f(x)=mx+b </m></p></statement>
    <answer><p><ol label="a">
        <li><p>Not always true (unless <m>b=0</m>): <m>f (1 + 2)\ne f (1) + f (2)</m> because <m>3m+b \ne 3m+2b </m>.</p></li>
        <li><p>Not always true: <m>f (1\cdot 2)\ne f (1)\cdot f (2)</m> because <m>2m+b \ne 2m^2 + 3mb + b^2 </m>.</p></li>
    </ol></p></answer>
    </exercise>

