<exercise number="67"><statement><p>Explain how the distributive law, <m>a(b + c) = ab + ac</m>, is different from the equation <m>f (a + b) = f (a) + f (b)</m> .</p></statement>
<answer><p>The distributive law shows a relationship between multiplication and addition that always holds. The equation <m>f (a + b) = f (a) + f (b)</m> is not about multiplication and may or may not be true.</p></answer>
